The antimatter quadrants for both light and dark sides of matter always reverses the positive and negative qualities of the turns. For example openness is the positive first Turn of light matter, yet openness is the negative Turn of antimatter. This continues for all four Turns. This anti definition within PTP continues to make the Particle Theory of Physics a good analogy. Because of this relationship between the matter and antimatter quadrants of the Spin Theory it is possible to pin some general characteristics to each of these quadrants. Namely that the matter side deals with scarcity. What we need to do or have work to do all fit within the scarcity mindset. The antimatter quadrant deals with that which we already possess. This is why openness becomes a negative characteristic on the antimatter quadrant. Being open with what we already possess will lead to a diminishing of those same possessions. For the same reason being open to new possibilities is positive on the matter quadrant because for that which we don’t already have we need to be open to possibilities for acquiring that which we need. A caveat here is that wanting something which we don’t need is influenced by the dark side quadrants and should be distinguished from our physical needs on the light side.

(Go into more detail about each turn and how it is different for the matter and antimatter quadrants.)

With four Turn dichotomies there are a total of 16 ways a personality Spin can be configured. However, up until now we have been speaking specifically about the matter or material side of the conscious mind. In addition to matter there is an antimatter configuration as well as both a matter and antimatter configuration for the unconscious mind. In regular particle physics light matter and dark matter are described. And the analogy can be extended to PTP as well. The light matter quadrant of personality is readily available for analysis by those who are interested to learn more. The quadrant of personality that is antimatter and on the light side is also accessible by observation, but is more difficult to perceive. This light side antimatter Spin can confuse and muddy perception for anyone seeking to find it. It is important to work through the process of identifying the true light side matter Turns to distinguish the correct display. The dark side matter can not be identified by normal conversation and can only be identified through access to the unconscious. This can be achieved through deep contemplation. Other methods such as hypnosis are very difficult to use because the hypnotist has the very powerful ability to suggest. Suggestion is the way hypnotists cause their patients to enter hypnosis and the only known method of interaction with another’s unconscious at this time. A hypnotized individual will form act upon and form conclusions based on the suggestions or commands they receive from the hypnotist. Therefore the true dark side matter and antimatter turns are usually only available to the individual themselves, through that meditation or deep contemplation.

Since each quadrant of the Spin personality definition has four dichotomous turns. Each therefore has the capability of being one of 16 types. With the four quadrants of the Spin theory there is one in 16 possibilities for each. Therefore there are 65,536 possible personalities for the Spin theory. This is far more complex then any current popular personality theory. However, despite having more possible options it can be recognized that depending on what the individual is focusing on it is possible to identify and even justify almost all personality theories in existence. With so many possibilities it is possible to find and prove how any one of them could fit with the PTP.

## Charge Theory

Now let’s move on to the charge theory of the full PTP. The charge theory is originated on personality systems based on threes or trichotomies. The Enneagram was the most fundamental to exploring charge. However before going straight into describing charge it is important to describe how to link from the Spin theory to the Charge theory. Below is an examination of the link.

In addition to the Up and Down Spin positions each neutrino has three ways of being in the Up or down position. These three ways of being in Spin are positive, negative, and neutral. Specifically this charge can be thought of as a path from the Up and Down Spin positions. Namely two of the turns change at a time through the path to go from Up to Down and the complementary path back from Down to Up. The neutrino does not pause halfway through this path, instead it is one continuous change two at a time, twice to go to the opposite Spin. if we look at the specific Turns in a Spin it is possible to see that with changing two at a time there are only three possible ways to achieve the full Spin. For the light matter side the Positive path through the Spin is to change the 1st and 3rd turns first followed by the 2nd and 4th. The Neutral Spin path is to change the 2nd and 3rd turns first followed by the 1st and 4th. Finally the negative path though the Spin is to change the 3rd and 4th first followed by the 1st and 2nd. 

Starting with the Charge theory a component of Will is engaged as a Charged personality will actually have the ability to Will a change from the Up position to the Down position. This is the path of Will that was described in the previous paragraph. In all actuality it is possible for the Spin to change in the Unwilled path as well, the direct compliment of the Willed path. So for the Positive path the Unwilled version is to have the 2nd and 4th Turns switch first followed by the 1st and 3rd. The Neutral and Negative paths have their own Unwilled versions as well.  Switching the 1st and 4th dichotomies first is the Neutral Unwilled path and switching the 1st and 2nd dichotomies first is the Negative Unwilled path.

An important note here is that for the antimatter quadrant the paths change. The negative path becomes the positive path and vice versa. The Neutral path stays the same, but for all three the Willed and Unwilled paths reverse as well.

(More details about what the paths look like for the antimatter and matter quadrants.)

A rule for the Neutrino theory is that the balance of positive and negative Turns will always be balanced. Therefore the Neutrino will always be neutral. Again starting with the Charge Theory positive and negative can become unbalanced. The following explains:

It is important to know which path the Spin takes because the combination of the light matter and dark matter quadrants of Spin create the full charge. No matter what path the Spin takes, that path is independent from the individual turns in the Up and Down positions. If the light and dark matter quadrants each have three possible positions then combined they create nine full charges. Those combined charges are given with the light matter half charge first followed by the dark matter half charge: neutral, neutral; neutral, positive; neutral, negative; positive, positive; positive, neutral; positive, negative; negative, negative; negative, neutral; and negative, positive. This leads to three full charges which are neutral, positive, and negative respectively. The Charge theory of PTP of necessity combines the light matter and dark matter quadrants into one. The light antimatter and dark antimatter combine into one as well generating its own set of nine possible combinations of full antimatter charges.

