## Color Theory

Following the Personality Charge Theory is Personality Color Theory. And again another level of Will is required here. This time instead of three charged paths between two options as in the Charge Theory, there are four colored pathways. In the Charge theory there were three possible paths, but only one was ever used. This resulted in only one fixed charge. However, in the personality Color theory instead of Spinning back and forth between two positions along a single charged pathway, of the four possible Colored pathways two are fixed as the path between three charged positions. The core Charge point as well as two auxiliary Charged points. Further while the Charge theory results in fermions with some kind of Charge whether that charge is positive, negative, or neutral, the fermions always seek to balance out their different Spins and Charges moving to the Color theory. As a result different from in the Spin theory where all possible options were exhausted, in Color theory only those pathways that are balanced by spin and charge are options. As a result there are only six possible colored triplets. Here they are enumerated: 135, 147, 279, 258, 468,  and 369. The fermion can be any one of the 9 possible charged particles, but it can only be one of these six triplets. Each number is represented in these triplets twice. Therefore the charged fermion itself can travel either in one or the other. For example if the fermion is the charged particle 1, then it can either travel through the 135 triplet or the 147 triplet. In addition, according to Color theory the pathway to light matter or consciousness can only be one of the other two numbers. This leads to second bifurcation of the color pathway. Taking the previous example one step further, if the fermion charged particle only travels on the 135 triplet, then it can either go to the 3rd charged point the 3 consciously or the 5th point consciously. This is a result of the combination between the light and dark matter. So it is possible to identify that the Charged particle is one of four possible Colored outcomes. It doesn’t matter which Charged particle the fermion is its color is independent.

Like before in the Charge Theory, Will is again presented as an option. This time there are two pathways between three charged points with one of the charged points between the other two. By Will it is possible to travel from the core point to the conscious point or to the unconscious point. Also it is possible to travel the path to the conscious and unconscious points by the Unwilled path. This time the core point travels to the conscious charged point through its wings. The wings of the core point are simply the charged points to its sides. For example the wings of the 6th charged point is 5 and 7, the two adjacent charged points. Both adjacent points are utilized, however one of them leads to the conscious point and the other to the unconscious point. In transforming into the conscious or unconscious point the Color, Charge, and Spin change.

(Give more details about the possible paths for each Charged point.)

This is how the Charged particle gives rise to the Colored particles. In the Color theory itself, the last quadrants of the Spin theory are combined. Charge Theory combined light and dark, the conscious and unconscious defining how a fermion accesses both. In Color theory antimatter now combines with matter to create the full Color. Both matter and antimatter have ascended from Charge as one of four possible outcomes independent of both Spin and Charge. Matter now has three possible states that it can occupy and Antimatter pairs with Matter having its own three states. As Matter changes from one to another of its possible Charged and Spinned state it changes Color. However it only changes color to compliment the change in Antimatter Color resulting in the two always pairing in three possible states.

These states are the conscious, unconscious, and the neutral or masked state. These states pull and stretch each other….

